article.description: Payton Henson scored 18 points and grabbed eight rebounds, and Trae Bell-Haynes had nine points and 10 assists as Vermont held off Marist 76-72 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Henson scores 18 to lead Vermont past Marist 76-72
article.linkText: Henson scores 18 to lead Vermont past Marist 76-72
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- Payton Henson scored 18 points and grabbed eight rebounds, and Trae Bell-Haynes had nine points and 10 assists as Vermont held off Marist 76-72 on Wednesday night. Anthony Lamb made a 3-pointer with 9:48 left to give Vermont a 55-45 lead. Marist went on a 14-4 run to tie it at 59 when Khallid Hart made a layup with 6:09 left. The Foxes took the lead 69-68 off Hart's steal and layup with 2:28 remaining. But Henson immediately responded with a layup off a feed from Bell-Haynes and the Catamounts never trailed again. Lamb finished with 13 points as both he and Henson each shot 6 of 10 from the floor. Dre Wills added 11 points off the bench for Vermont (2-1). The Catamounts raced to an 18-9 lead and led 37-29 at intermission after forcing Marist into 12 first-half turnovers. Hart scored 21 for Marist (0-3) on 7-of-14 shooting while contributing five assists and five steals.
